• Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. PRETORIA – The South African Revenue Service (SARS) will release the revenue collection for 2017/18 financial year. In February, SARS announced that it has crossed the psychological threshold of the R1-trillion mark in its revenue collection efforts, making it the third year in a row that it has reached this milestone. READ: Moyane must be held to account and face prison time: Corruption Watch Last month, SARS announced that under the Special Voluntary Disclosure Programme (SVDP), non-compliant taxpayers with unauthorised foreign assets and income have to date entered into agreements with the revenue collection to the value of over R3,3-billion in tax liabilities. SARS said, in terms of the agreements reached, these taxpayers have already paid over R2,7-billion and the Revenue Service expects another R580-million to be paid by the end of March. eNCA